oulakis shows that Kafka can give us invaluable insights into how to be free—and how to laugh.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 07. Mrz 2024) 0aFree will and determinism in literature. 0aLiberty in literature. 4aLiterature : Literary Criticism. 4aPhilosophy : Continental Philosophy. 4aPhilosophy : Philosophy of Literature. 4aPhilosophy : Philosophy. 4aPolitics and Law : Political Philosophy. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Free Will & Determinism.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package 2016z978311149098440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143846241740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438462417423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438462417/original  a978-3-11-149098-4  SUNY Press eBook Package 2016b2016  aGBV-deGruyter-alles